TY  - JOUR
T1  - Pooling, Access, and Countervailing Power in Channel Governance
AU  - Hendrikse, George
Y1  - 2011/06/30
PY  - 2011
DA  - 2011/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.1110.1369
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.1110.1369
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1692
EP  - 1702
VL  - 57
IS  - 9
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Fruit and vegetable marketing organization the Greenery has experienced various governance structure changes, like horizontal merger, forward integration, and the emergence of grower associations. A multilateral incomplete contracting model is presented to account for these changes by analysing the interactions between pooling, access, and countervailing power. This model does not only explain the changes at the Greenery, but it contributes also to the design of efficient channel governance. This paper was accepted by Pradeep Chintagunta and Preyas Desai, special issue editors. This paper was accepted by Pradeep Chintagunta and Preyas Desai, special issue editors.
